<PLUGIN name="unraid-zram-card" author="John White" version="2026.05.05.02" launch="Settings/UnraidZramCard" pluginURL="https://gitlab.johnpwhite.com/johner/unraid-zram-card/-/raw/master/unraid-zram-card.plg" min="6.12.1" support="https://forums.unraid.net/topic/196763-new-plugin-created-zram/" icon="unraid-zram-card.png">

<CHANGES>
## 2026.05.05.02
- Fix: tier-observability follow-up (smoke regression in 2026.05.05.01). The new smoke assertion 9 hard-failed on test servers without a Tier 2 swap file configured because "overflow only" was only rendered inside the if-block guarded by ssd_swap_path. Empty-state copy now reads "Runs at priority 10 — overflow only, never used while Tier 1 has room" so the priority explainer surfaces before the user configures anything (better UX, more discoverable, fixes the smoke). PHPUnit guard tightened from substring presence to substr_count &gt;= 2 so a future refactor cannot drop one branch silently — the current 3 occurrences (active row, inactive row, empty-state) all stay.
## 2026.05.05.01
- Feat: tier observability — surface live used bytes per swap tier and address forum-asked questions about per-tier swappiness and priority customisation. Settings page Tier 1 status row now shows "Used: X / Y · algo · priority N — used first" instead of just allocated size. Tier 2 status row shows "Used: X / Y · priority 10 — overflow only" when active, file-only-state when inactive. Swappiness input gains a clarifier line: "Global kernel setting — applies to swap as a whole, not per-tier. Tier order is controlled by priority, not swappiness" — this is the UX answer to "can I have a Tier 2 swappiness?" without building a misleading control (vm.swappiness is system-wide; no per-device knob exists in the kernel). Priority explainers ("used first" / "overflow only") inline in each status row are the UX answer to "can we customise priority?" without exposing an editable control that would break the load-bearing 100/10 ordering. Collector schema gains an "s" field (Tier 2 used in bytes) sampled from `swapon --bytes --show=NAME,USED` filtered to ssd_swap_path; 0 when unconfigured/inactive. Forward-compatible: dashboard JS reads pre-upgrade history entries (no s) the same as new ones. Spec: docs/specs/TIER_OBSERVABILITY.md. Tests: TierObservabilityTest.php (7 assertions on status JSON shape, collector schema, page UX text), zram-card.test.js gains 3 cases for the new s field (kept with s, kept without s for forward-compat, dropped on partial writes), smoke.sh assertion 6 extended with a soft Tier 2 s-field count and new assertion 9 hard-fails if any of the three UX clarifier strings disappear from the rendered settings page. Full suite: 27 PHPUnit tests / 98 assertions, 17 Vitest tests, 9 smoke assertions — all green locally.
## 2026.05.04.01
- Feat: tier observability — surface live used bytes per swap tier and address forum-asked questions about per-tier swappiness and priority customisation. Settings page Tier 1 status row now shows "Used: X / Y · algo · priority N — used first" instead of just allocated size. Tier 2 status row shows "Used: X / Y · priority 10 — overflow only" when active, file-only-state when inactive. Swappiness input gains a clarifier line: "Global kernel setting — applies to swap as a whole, not per-tier. Tier order is controlled by priority, not swappiness" — this is the UX answer to "can I have a Tier 2 swappiness?" without building a misleading control (vm.swappiness is system-wide; no per-device knob exists in the kernel). Priority explainers ("used first" / "overflow only") inline in each status row are the UX answer to "can we customise priority?" without exposing an editable control that would break the load-bearing 100/10 ordering. Collector schema gains an "s" field (Tier 2 used in bytes) sampled from `swapon --bytes --show=NAME,USED` filtered to ssd_swap_path; 0 when unconfigured/inactive. Forward-compatible: dashboard JS reads pre-upgrade history entries (no s) the same as new ones. Spec: docs/specs/TIER_OBSERVABILITY.md. Tests: TierObservabilityTest.php (7 assertions on status JSON shape, collector schema, page UX text), zram-card.test.js gains 3 cases for the new s field (kept with s, kept without s for forward-compat, dropped on partial writes), smoke.sh assertion 6 extended with a soft Tier 2 s-field count and new assertion 9 hard-fails if any of the three UX clarifier strings disappear from the rendered settings page. Full suite: 27 PHPUnit tests / 98 assertions, 17 Vitest tests, 9 smoke assertions — all green locally.
## 2026.05.03.01
- Fix two state-sync bugs in zram management. (1) remove_zram silently swallowed swapoff and zramctl --reset exit codes, then unlinked device.conf and reported success regardless. Under memory pressure that left the kernel device active while the UI lost track, producing the user-reported "REMOVE button persists across reloads" symptom. Both commands are now guarded with !== 0 checks; on failure we report the real error and keep state intact. Added wipefs -a between them so the swap signature is actively cleared, and switched zram_get_our_device() to blkid -c /dev/null to bypass the persistent /run/blkid/blkid.tab cache (zramctl --reset fires no udev change event, so the cache could lag reality for several seconds). (2) create_zram read size_mode, percent, and algo only from saved config, so a slider tweak made before clicking CREATE was silently ignored — user reported "I cannot set Auto Size to 75%, it always creates 16G; turns out you have to APPLY &amp; SAVE first". CREATE now accepts these as live query params from the form, validates them (custom size must match /^\d+[GMT]$/i, algo must be in the kernel allow-list), and persists what was actually used so next-boot init.sh reproduces it. Specs: docs/specs/REMOVE_ZRAM_STATE_SYNC.md, docs/specs/CREATE_ZRAM_LIVE_PARAMS.md. Tests: RemoveZramSilentFailureTest.php and CreateZramLiveParamsTest.php (20 assertions, all green). Also fixed phpstan.neon excludePaths so analysis can run (marked src/tests and src/vendor optional with (?))
## 2026.04.28.02
- Fix: complete the Tier 2 rename pass — body description, dashboard tier label (ZRAM + Disk), drive-row labels (Disk idle/off/active), action toasts (No disk swap file found / Disk swap file removed), init-script log messages, and README.public.md user-facing copy. v01 missed everything outside the section heading; user reported the description still said SSD swap file. Internal identifiers (config keys ssd_swap_*, ZRAM_CARD_SSD label, bash SSD_PATH var) preserved as stable identifiers.
## 2026.04.28.01
- Feat: Extend vm.swappiness range to 0-200 (kernel 5.8+) and bump default to 150 for zram-priority swap topology. Settings UI shows tier guidance under the input. Fix: drop unsupported HDD parity-interference warning, replace with honest random-IO impact note that acknowledges bad swap beats OOM. Fix: Tier 2 drive picker label and empty-state copy updated to be inclusive of HDD-only users - picker already accepts cache pool HDDs but previous copy implied SSD-only. Tests: new PHPUnit assertion for 180 and 200 round-trip through config layer; smoke updated to use 175 (a value impossible to test before this change).
## 2026.04.20.01
- Archive zram_swap.php: replaced with inert stub; file was dead code superseded by zram_actions.php and had no CSRF validation, used REQUEST variables directly without escaping
- Add CSRF validation to view_log and view_cmd_log actions in zram_actions.php; previously these log-read endpoints were exempt from the CSRF gate but can leak config details to cross-origin requests
- Add csrf_token parameter to view_log and view_cmd_log AJAX calls in zram-settings.js to match new server-side gate
- Update TIERED_SWAP_MANAGER.md status from Draft to Approved; all requirements and Appendix A bugs are shipped
- Update L4_VISUAL_TESTS.md status from Draft to In Progress; core flow shipped in v2026.04.18.04
## 2026.04.18.07
- Fix: Plugin uninstall hook no longer wipes user settings from /boot/config/plugins/unraid-zram-card. Caught by the new L3 uninstall smoke test, which asserts flash config survives uninstall per Unraid convention. Users can now uninstall and reinstall without losing refresh interval, compression algorithm choice, swappiness, or SSD swap configuration.
## 2026.04.18.06
- Chore: Supersedes 2026.04.18.05 which was an accidental publish from a pipeline dry-run test. No functional changes to plugin source. Workspace root receives three new pre-publish guards: PLG FILE URL manifest drift check, src tree leak audit for secrets and bloat, and a proper --dry-run flag on publish-factory so this particular mistake cannot repeat.
## 2026.04.18.05
- dry-run-test
## 2026.04.18.04
- Fix: Chart tooltip no longer overflows horizontally into adjacent stat cards when hovering near the right edge of the graph. Clamps tooltip left-edge to the chart bounding box. Caught by the new L4 visual-review layer.
- Feat: Introduce L4 visual regression testing — a Haiku+Chrome-MCP subagent drives the dashboard via a playbook, captures screenshots at known interaction states, and pipes each through Gemini 3 Flash with a ZRAM-scoped correctness prompt. Aggregates findings into tests/visual_review.sh, failing on high-severity issues.
- Docs: docs/specs/L4_VISUAL_TESTS.md describes the architecture, auth handling, and prompt-tuning discipline. tests/ui_e2e_playbook.md gives the Haiku subagent step-by-step instructions including the Windows path gotcha.
## 2026.04.18.03
- Fix: Chart tooltip no longer clips when hovering in the lower half of the graph. Replaced the canvas-drawn Chart.js tooltip with an external HTML div floated on document.body, so it can extend beyond the chart's 70px height. Positions above the caret by default; flips below if there is no room. Built with safe DOM methods (no innerHTML).
## 2026.04.18.02
- Feat: Introduce layered test suite. Layer 1 is static analysis via phpstan.neon and eslintrc.json. Layer 2 is PHPUnit plus Vitest unit tests covering config read-write, cache-buster regression, history-schema filter, and the rounded-bytes formatter. Layer 3 is an SSH smoke suite with 6 assertions that run against the live server after install.
- Refactor: zram-card.js extracts formatBytes, formatBytesRound, and filterHistory to module scope with a conditional CommonJS export, so Vitest can import them without disturbing browser behaviour.
- Refactor: The dashboard IIFE now bails early when the zramChart element is absent, preventing polling timers from running in test or non-dashboard contexts.
- Refactor: zram_config.php uses defined() guards so the module is safe to re-include under test bootstrap overrides.
- Docs: docs/specs/TEST_SUITE.md describes the three layers, smoke exit codes, and rollback policy.
## 2026.04.18.01
- Feat: Dashboard graph Y-axis labels now round to the nearest 5 in their natural unit (MB/GB/etc) via a new formatBytesRound helper. Stat cards still show precise values through formatBytes.
## 2026.04.17.06
- Feat: Uncompressed layer recoloured from slate-navy to muted amber (c46b36 border, d49373 card text) with lower fill alpha (0.32). Slate was too cold and heavy; amber conveys the theoretical RAM cost without overpowering the green compressed layer.
## 2026.04.17.05
- Feat: Uncompressed layer recoloured from forest green to deep slate-navy (34495e fill, 7b8da3 card text). Monochromatic two-green palette was muddy. Slate back recedes and contrasts, so the bright green Compressed layer pops as the live value.
## 2026.04.17.04
- Feat: Uncompressed layer/card changed to dark forest green (3a5a2f fill, a8c79a text) so the two layers share a hue family. Saved RAM is now visually intuitive as the gap between dark and light green.
## 2026.04.17.03
- Feat: Compressed layer/card colour changed to green (7fba59) for better contrast against the dark-slate uncompressed back layer.
## 2026.04.17.02
- Fix: Settings form POST silently dropped because action hardcoded to /Settings/UnraidZramCard while page is Menu=Utilities. Now submits to self.
- Fix: Dashboard cache-buster was a hardcoded 2026.04.16 string, so browsers kept serving the old zram-card.js after upgrade. Replaced with filemtime of the asset file so it auto-invalidates on every install.
## 2026.04.17.01
- Feat: Dashboard graph now shows uncompressed memory (dark slate, back) and compressed memory (cyan, front) as stacked filled layers. The gap between them is the visible RAM saved.
- Feat: CPU load line remains overlaid on top (right axis, red).
- Feat: Stats cards reworked to match graph. Dropped RAM Saved card (now visually intrinsic in the graph gap). Added Uncompressed card. Renamed Actual Used to Compressed.
- Refactor: Collector history schema updated from t/s/l to t/o/u/l so the dashboard can plot uncompressed and compressed values over time.
- Fix: Frontend gracefully skips legacy history entries missing the new fields to avoid chart glitches on upgrade.
## 2026.04.16.09
- Fix: Drive picker only shows mounts under /mnt/. Excludes Docker, libvirt, tmpfs, and zram-backed mounts that are unsuitable for swap files.
## 2026.04.16.08
- Fix: Move chmod 600 after dd to prevent insecure permissions warning on swap file creation
## 2026.04.16.07
- Fix: Detect btrfs RAID in drive picker and warn that swap files are not supported. Clean up swap dir on failure.
## 2026.04.16.06
- Fix: Handle btrfs swap files with NOCOW attribute. Unraid cache pools use btrfs which requires chattr +C before swap file creation.
## 2026.04.16.05
- Fix: Move all settings JS to external file to avoid Markdown parser escaping inline script tags in page files
